I came from the 30 days of yoga series. I spent a few days in between just doing yoga for my hips as they were bugging me, but missed the variety these little 30 day challenges bring. I was trying to decide which challenge to do, and yoga camp frightened me in particular because of day 2, 50 minutes of yoga. In 30 days of yoga I found I got to a point where I thought way too much about "how much time is left", but I think yesterday "accepting" that time was a factor, and accepting that I had to move past that, I got through today with ease. I believe I checked the time stamp twice, not necessarily to see 'how much time is left?' but how much time had passed as I was shocked that I was able to think so little about it. 
I'm very proud of myself for this, and just wanted to share just incase anyone else might be a bit fearful over the time stamp on this practice. Once it is out of your mind, it will fly by. Enjoy the moments as they come.

I am here after doing a different 30 day yoga challenge of yours, so really this is day 32, and I am truly learning SO much. about yoga, and about myself. In terms of yoga, I am really beginning to notice a yoga 'personality'. Sometimes I come to the mat and feel playful, like today, and I was recognising that I didn't need some of the child pose rests and so adapted it to what I did need. Others, I am there to relax or to switch off. I enjoy the practice so much, and I really could have done this for hours today to begin with, but as the practice went on I became relaxed, content and sleepy - it's 11:30pm here, so I will be going to sleep now :) I have also learnt a lot about myself. When I come to the mat, I truly check in with myself and reflect on how I am *actually* feeling. I have realised that so often I have convinced myself to feel a way that others would want me to feel, or that I think I should feel or would be expected to feel. Through yoga, I have learnt how I really do feel and have learnt a lot about myself through this. I say this to you a lot, but honestly, thank you so so much - yoga has been a life changing experience for me X

‚úîÔ∏è I create space in my heart, I create compassion for myself, I create patience for growth üôè I was feeling all kinds of sassy today during the foot balance portions haha! But it's so true that we often forget to "own it." In the context of practice (or even extended to life): we are where we are, and we begin where we are; so why not have fun and create joy where we are? It can be so easy to forget why we started doing something if our reason is somewhat superficial. I started yoga for many deeper reasons that help me go through and enjoy the practices each day. I still have days where I'll lose sight of the focus, feel kinda challenged, feel overwhelmed--feel human--but that reminds me that this is why it's called daily practice. One day at a time, because anything worth doing takes time :) Namaste everyone and thank you for practice Adriene üíúüåûüôè

I really wanted to leave a thank you comment. My back, hip, and knee have been hurting since my early twenties (I am in my late 30s now) . In the fall of 2017, my body was in the worst shape ever due to a traumatic experience that lead me to rely on alcohol for about 3 years. I was desperate to change everything, so I relocated myself to a totally different place and retired. Even after I moved, I still had very bad back pain, so one day I googled "yoga for back pain" and that was my first day of yoga. I felt better and better every time I would do it, so I ended up doing yoga for about half an year, 3~4 times a week. I really felt like I was a different person. But reality came back to me and I got lazy, I did not need to do yoga because my body did not hurt anymore. Couple of days ago, I felt a cramp in my back and it made me so scary at first. But I knew where to go and have came back to "Yoga Camp." It is only my second day, but it is a great to come back and re-experience the small but amazing changes in my body. I am so grateful to you and all the efforts you put into these unbelievable contents. Thank you.

I know I'm a little late on this yoga camp but I tried the first one Adrienne posted last year (i think it was last year) and stopped the second day because I didn't think I had time, so I did a few of her yoga videos here and there when I wanted to take time for myself (which really wasn't very often). I decided instead of taking time for myself by watching netflix or scrolling on social media worrying about other people's lives I TRULY take time for myself and check in with where I am at body mind and soul. Although I am in the second day...I feel a little lighter.

 I didn't think I would be able to do 50 minutes, i got a bit impatient/bored halway through but that was because I was going through the motions and not checking in as often, in the last 20 minutes I got into my rhythm of breathing again and being present and the time flew by. I will continue to work on my presence during camp because it really does feel good. 

My inner mantra began with "I create peace" and then changed to " I create opportunities for myself" and finally "I create space" I went between the opportunity and space mantra because I have had a very stressful time balancing work, school and things going on at home. 

My first day was a bit difficult I'm not going to lie, I worked a 12 hour shift and I was very stressed, sitting quitely and being still for a couple of minutes caused a bit of anxiety. However I trusted the video and accepted where I was and it was crazy how quickly my shallow breaths became deeper and deeper and how in control I felt. My second day i learned a lot about where I am at physically, this really makes it easy to go through the motions of your day. For example when I focused on my feet during camp (using all four corners), I would also be aware of my feet when I was standing in the kitchen or sitting at my desk. When I focused on my breathing and posture, I really felt a difference in the way I carried myself. All in all so far so good... I can't wait for tomorrow and I know I will do it tomorrow! I have a really busy Monday and Tuesday (12 hour days) however I think I can squeeze in some time before i go to bed!
